Because this was caused by an imported module, the [Using with webpack guide](https://jestjs.io/docs/en/webpack) gave me a detailed guidance on what to do with non-js imported modules.

I used [`identity-obj-proxy`](https://github.com/keyz/identity-obj-proxy) to mock my CSS modules, and a local `fileMock.js` to define mocking of other non-JS modules:
```javascript
// __mocks__/fileMock.js
